  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!\r\n\r\nIf the matter is security related, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nIn the [code path](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/search?q=NewOAuthConfig&unscoped_q=NewOAuthConfig) to acquire AAD token, because of the inclusion of the API version in the URLs for authorization, the returned token is not compatible with many AAD scenarios like OIDC and On-Behalf-Of flow.\r\n\r\nThere is a long list of issues documenting this problem:\r\nhttps://github.com/Azure/go-autorest/issues/277\r\nhttps://github.com/Azure/go-autorest/issues/321\r\nhttps://github.com/AzureAD/azure-activedirectory-library-for-nodejs/issues/128\r\nhttps://github.com/AzureAD/azure-activedirectory-library-for-python/pull/57\r\nhttps://github.com/Azure/aks-engine/issues/376\r\n\r\nThe fix is pretty simple, use [this api](https://github.com/Azure/go-autorest/blob/2913f263500c4a5b23dada1b46ccd22ac972315f/autorest/adal/config.go#L56) with `apiVersion` set to `nil`.\r\n\r\nThis incompatible behavior impacts \r\nhttps://github.com/appscode/guard/issues/131\r\nhttps://github.com/appscode/guard/issues/235\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nFollow the [official documentation](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/active-directory/develop/v1-protocols-oauth-code#use-the-authorization-code-to-request-an-access-token) to acquire AAD token \r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nuse kubectl to get AAD token, paste token into https://jwt.ms/ and verify the audience claim\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): all versions\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g: `cat /etc/os-release`):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Network plugin and version (if this is a network-related bug):\r\n- Others:\r\n",
